rounds.response:
I can win immediately on the diagonal 4-8 (I already have O in both squares) if I secure 0, but that’s already taken, so let me look elsewhere.

Looking at the major diagonal (top-left 0→bottom-right 8): X|O|O isn’t a threat.  
The minor diagonal (top-right 2→bottom-left 6) is O|O|X – leaves me no winning line there.  
Row-wise: first row is already full. Middle row has O| | . Bottom row is X| |O.  
Column-wise: left column X|3|X, middle X|O|7, right column O|5|O.

The third column already has two O’s (2 and 8) and the only open spot left in that column is 5.  
So [5] would complete

2 |   | 5  
\   /   \   /
  O   O   O

giving three O’s vertically and the win!

[5]
